-- variation: PlumeClam41497

-- Describe a short walk used to estimate the solution to
-- a Poisson equation Δu = f, which involves both boundary
-- samples x and source samples y.

Step x0, x1, x2, x3
Step y0, y1, y2, y3

Next(x0,x1)
Next(x1,x2)
Next(x2,x3)
y0 := sourceSample(x0)
y1 := sourceSample(x1)
y2 := sourceSample(x2)
y3 := sourceSample(x3)

AutoLabel All
Label x2 "…"
Label x3 "xk"
NoLabel y2
NoLabel y3


